iate", "Birmingham", "Phone: 205-581-1571", "Fax: 205-581-0799", "wsmithart@lightfootlaw.com", "PRACTICE AREAS Wesley Smithart brings advocacy experience to her", "defense litigation work.", "Appellate", "Wesley puts the knowledge she gained in law school and as a Lightfoot", "Automotive", "summer associate to work every day for her clients. She has worked on", "Environmental & Toxic Torts", "cases involving product liability, personal injury, white-collar criminal", "Product Liability", "defense, environmental/toxic tort and other issues.", "White-Collar Criminal Defense", "& Corporate Investigations After graduating from Huntingdon College where she served as Student", "Government Association president, Wesley earned a Masters of", "EDUCATION Theological Studies with a concentration in human rights from Emory", "University in Atlanta. At Emory, Wesley honed her interest in the legal", "University of Alabama School of system by teaching a course on restorative justice in a women\u2019s prison", "cum Law (J.D., laude, 2020) and interning for a drug court program.", "Emory University, Candler", "During her third year at the University of Alabama School of Law,", "School of Theology (M.T.S.,", "Wesley worked in its Domestic Violence Law Clinic, representing clients 2017)", "in court for a variety of proceedings, including protection from abuse Huntingdon College (B.A.,", "actions, divorces and child custody cases. This work gave her magna cum laude, 2015)", "invaluable courtroom experience that she draws on at Lightfoot.", "BAR ADMISSIONS", "Alabama Law Wesley was the special works editor for the Review,", "president of the Alabama Law Student Alumni Society and a member of", "Alabama (2020) the John A. Campbell Moot Court Board while in law school. She", "achieved top accolades in her courses on appellate advocacy, trial", "advocacy and remedies.", "Wesley grew up in Union Springs, Alabama, and now spends time", "exploring all that downtown Birmingham has to offer. S